1 packet Crumbed Chicken Breast Strips
1 tomato
½ head cos lettuce
6 packet Mini Flour Tortillas
1 garlic aioli
olive oil

Heat a large frying pan over
medium-high heat with a
generous drizzle of olive
oil. Cook crumbed chicken
breast strips until golden
and cooked through,
3-4 minutes each side.
Season, slice and set aside.

While chicken is cooking,
thinly slice tomato into
half-moons. Roughly chop
cos lettuce (see ingredients).

Spread each mini flour
tortilla with some garlic
aioli. Top with tomato,
cooked chicken and cos
lettuce. Tightly roll into a
wrap.

FRESH TIP: Use leftover cos lettuce in a salad!